wikipedia_page.main: David William Baker (born 26 July 1935) is an English former professional cricketer active 1961–65. Baker was born in Kingston upon Hull. He was a legbreak and googly bowler who played in 34 first-class cricket matches in his career.After signing for Kent County Cricket Club in 1959 he made his senior debut for the side in 1961. Baker played 27 times for Kent between 1961 and the end of the 1963 season before moving to Nottinghamshire. He played seven times in two seasons for Notts before being released by the club.
